						               													<description>&amp;quot;RACECRAZE:  A Strategic, Fun-Filled Racing Game!&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A Nascar-like themed racing game from a small publisher. The mechanics of this game are simple: &amp;quot;Qualifying&amp;quot; position is based on random card draw. Each turn, roll three (standard) dice, and optionally roll two more &amp;quot;special dice&amp;quot; (33% +3, 33% -3, 33% take a card). Move your car on the track (16 spaces to 20 spaces around from inside to outside track; no track &amp;quot;choke points&amp;quot;) by the total amount. Cards either move car forward, backward, or force player &amp;quot;into the pit&amp;quot; before proceeding. Player turn order is re-ranked each turn by position+laps, and each race (of 5) ends after a predetermined number of laps.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is awarded a number of points at the conclusion of each race based on finishing position. Winner has the most points after the fifth race.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
